WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.230 --> 00:00:12.070
La Monte Yarroll: I'm Lamont Henry Piggy Yarrell. This is my Syracuse University Master's in Applied Data Science portfolio.

2
00:00:12.860 --> 00:00:15.009
La Monte Yarroll: I am a data hamster.

3
00:00:15.270 --> 00:00:18.740
La Monte Yarroll: I've hoarded my own data and ideas for years.

4
00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:24.960
La Monte Yarroll: Turning this data into actionable insights is a motivating factor in getting my degree in data science.

5
00:00:26.280 --> 00:00:30.410
La Monte Yarroll: I'm going to discuss 3 projects. The Name Navigator.

6
00:00:30.650 --> 00:00:33.990
La Monte Yarroll: Sugar Bowl, in which we introduce glycemic increment.

7
00:00:34.260 --> 00:00:36.230
La Monte Yarroll: And the synoptic Key of Life.

8
00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:44.670
La Monte Yarroll: The Name Navigator is a SQL package to encode cultural awareness of naming practices.

9
00:00:46.780 --> 00:00:48.870
La Monte Yarroll: This is the conceptual model.

10
00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:52.659
La Monte Yarroll: Names are made of particles like Yarl, or piggy.

11
00:00:52.870 --> 00:01:01.630
La Monte Yarroll: Each particle is represented in the target alphabet, in a Latinized form, and in the International Phonetic Alphabet for pronunciation.

12
00:01:02.380 --> 00:01:11.649
La Monte Yarroll: The order and use are locale-specific. For instance, in Georgian, formal address is Baton or Kalbaton.

13
00:01:11.760 --> 00:01:13.659
La Monte Yarroll: Followed by given name.

14
00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:19.029
La Monte Yarroll: Unlike English, where it is Mr. or Ms. followed by last name.

15
00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:28.829
La Monte Yarroll: This is the logical model, which you can compare to the conceptual model at your own leisure.

16
00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.060
La Monte Yarroll: Here's an excerpt from the UI wireframes.

17
00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:38.120
La Monte Yarroll: This shows the 3 encodings of my name.

18
00:01:38.460 --> 00:01:42.399
La Monte Yarroll: particles in Georgian has spoken in Georgia.

19
00:01:42.970 --> 00:01:47.869
La Monte Yarroll: All nouns end in a vowel, so Lamont becomes Lamonte.

20
00:01:48.360 --> 00:01:54.409
La Monte Yarroll: Also, there are no diphthongs in Georgian, so yarl becomes Iaroli.

21
00:01:55.540 --> 00:02:01.799
La Monte Yarroll: This package is available with a permissive license for use in customer relationship management systems.

22
00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:09.219
La Monte Yarroll: Second is the Sugar Bowl project, in which we introduce the glycemic increment metric.

23
00:02:09.949 --> 00:02:13.390
La Monte Yarroll: This is a text mining project in individual medicine.

24
00:02:13.740 --> 00:02:16.399
La Monte Yarroll: This is joint work with Jen Velasi.

25
00:02:19.030 --> 00:02:23.800
La Monte Yarroll: A CGM is a medical device which records blood glucose every 5 minutes.

26
00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:31.579
La Monte Yarroll: On the right, we see the app. The green dots are meal records. I've been collecting data on every meal for several years now.

27
00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:40.549
La Monte Yarroll: Here is an initial analysis of the meal descriptions. You can see I eat a lot of peanut butter and cheese.

28
00:02:41.150 --> 00:02:44.970
La Monte Yarroll: Internet points to anyone who can spot my favorite restaurants.

29
00:02:47.930 --> 00:02:55.019
La Monte Yarroll: Our goal is to predict the blood sugar consequences of the meals and portions that the patient actually consumes.

30
00:02:55.280 --> 00:03:06.470
La Monte Yarroll: The standard metrics for this, glycemic index and glycemic load, are based on fasting conditions, standardized portions, and are normalized over a population.

31
00:03:06.860 --> 00:03:14.489
La Monte Yarroll: By contrast, glycemic increment applies to actual foods and portions which the patient consumes.

32
00:03:14.870 --> 00:03:18.410
La Monte Yarroll: Glycemic increment is the area under the glucose curve.

33
00:03:18.540 --> 00:03:24.310
La Monte Yarroll: Starting at the level at the start of the meal, and continuing for several hours.

34
00:03:29.550 --> 00:03:35.080
La Monte Yarroll: We applied text mining methods to extract terms and their glycemic increment consequences.

35
00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:41.809
La Monte Yarroll: We can see that things like donuts, croissants, and dried fruits all cause large swings of glycemic increment.

36
00:03:42.460 --> 00:03:57.599
La Monte Yarroll: Fluids with glycemic increment near zero are peanut butter, cashews, and cottage cheese with peach preserves. It is interesting that the small quantity of peach preserves eaten with cottage cheese has a negligible effect.

37
00:03:58.810 --> 00:04:09.509
La Monte Yarroll: Individualized medicine is a growing field. The availability of inexpensive sensors that can provide information from activity, blood pressure, blood oxygen, and blood glucose.

38
00:04:09.650 --> 00:04:11.840
La Monte Yarroll: Has created a plethora of data.

39
00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:17.990
La Monte Yarroll: Patients can use their own data to produce suitable guidance for controlling blood sugar through diet.

40
00:04:20.899 --> 00:04:23.660
La Monte Yarroll: The last project is the Synoptic Key of Life.

41
00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:31.559
La Monte Yarroll: The goal is to make species descriptions in the open access and public domain mycological literature accessible to the amateur.

42
00:04:31.670 --> 00:04:34.450
La Monte Yarroll: We built this project over 5 courses.

43
00:04:34.720 --> 00:04:36.940
La Monte Yarroll: These are my collaborators.

44
00:04:39.810 --> 00:04:45.399
La Monte Yarroll: Here's an overview of the skull architecture as seen through the classes which implemented components.

45
00:04:45.520 --> 00:04:49.309
La Monte Yarroll: I'll concentrate mainly on machine learning and AI models.

46
00:04:49.610 --> 00:04:53.020
La Monte Yarroll: On the left, we have the websites that we scrape for articles.

47
00:04:53.140 --> 00:05:02.990
La Monte Yarroll: The dark blue block on the right is a PySpark pipeline that builds a classifier to extract species names and their descriptions from the literature.

48
00:05:03.950 --> 00:05:09.010
La Monte Yarroll: These names and descriptions are combined into taxa objects in the light blue box.

49
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:14.479
La Monte Yarroll: The taxa are then processed in two separate paths.

50
00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:21.990
La Monte Yarroll: The upper path uses an embedding into a searchable semantic space through the SBIRT small language model.

51
00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:28.870
La Monte Yarroll: This embedding is then used to find taxa that are similar to a description provided by the user.

52
00:05:29.950 --> 00:05:34.580
La Monte Yarroll: The lower path uses a different small language model, Mistral 7B,

53
00:05:34.730 --> 00:05:43.160
La Monte Yarroll: Which translates the freeform text description into a hierarchical representation of features, subfeatures, and values.

54
00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:50.939
La Monte Yarroll: There's representations are refined through constrained decoding, which limits the output to valid JSON structures.

55
00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:57.770
La Monte Yarroll: The vocabulary is then normalized through similarity to published ontologies.

56
00:05:59.050 --> 00:06:02.369
La Monte Yarroll: Finally, we have the website built with Django and React.

57
00:06:04.070 --> 00:06:06.360
La Monte Yarroll: Here's the search page from the website.

58
00:06:07.020 --> 00:06:10.480
La Monte Yarroll: Here we have an in-progress description built by the user.

59
00:06:10.650 --> 00:06:14.240
La Monte Yarroll: On the right, we have a set of tools for refining the description.

60
00:06:16.550 --> 00:06:28.720
La Monte Yarroll: This is a search result page. We have the full species name and description from the literature. We also provide links to a local PDF, if it is available, and the link back to the original source.

61
00:06:31.540 --> 00:06:34.119
La Monte Yarroll: This is the simplest of the feature tools.

62
00:06:34.250 --> 00:06:40.800
La Monte Yarroll: Which creates nested menus based on the JSON hierarchical representation of descriptions.

63
00:06:41.190 --> 00:06:45.200
La Monte Yarroll: This is a static set of menus and is not tied to the current description.

64
00:06:47.290 --> 00:06:56.420
La Monte Yarroll: These two tools are based on decision tree models built on the fly from the top few taxa that mostly closely match the current description.

65
00:06:56.860 --> 00:07:06.419
La Monte Yarroll: The decision tree on the left is based on just the text of the taxi descriptions. The decision tree on the right is based on the hierarchical JSON representation.

66
00:07:08.420 --> 00:07:14.549
La Monte Yarroll: The final feature tool helps the user collect statistics for microscopic features, like spores.

67
00:07:14.890 --> 00:07:17.489
La Monte Yarroll: It keeps a permanent record of every management.

68
00:07:17.780 --> 00:07:22.849
La Monte Yarroll: The count of the samples, N, turns green once it gets to 30.

69
00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:30.289
La Monte Yarroll: Metrics can be one-dimensional, for example, length of parapheses, They're two-dimensional, for example, spores.

70
00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:35.049
La Monte Yarroll: 2D measurements can also report Q value, ratio of length to width.

71
00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:43.110
La Monte Yarroll: A Q value of 1.0 indicates round spores. Higher Q values indicate more elongated spores.

72
00:07:43.320 --> 00:07:47.540
La Monte Yarroll: A taxonomist can add whatever measurable feature they care to.

73
00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:54.039
La Monte Yarroll: Website also includes typical features like account and settings management.

74
00:07:54.860 --> 00:08:00.340
La Monte Yarroll: My aspiration for the site is to get more people doing descriptive taxonomy for fungi.

75
00:08:01.070 --> 00:08:03.689
La Monte Yarroll: The website is currently in alpha test.

76
00:08:04.670 --> 00:08:09.100
La Monte Yarroll: I have several small projects planned to improve the classifier before I'll…

77
00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:12.130
La Monte Yarroll: Be happy taking this to beta.

78
00:08:16.240 --> 00:08:24.190
La Monte Yarroll: My master's program has exposed me a wide variety of topics, allowing me to turn my hoard of ideas and data into actionable insight.

79
00:08:24.380 --> 00:08:29.940
La Monte Yarroll: I've introduced my fellow students to the subtleties of managing names in a software system.

80
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:33.900
La Monte Yarroll: I'm still using the Sugar Bowl project for my meal planning.

81
00:08:34.360 --> 00:08:38.689
La Monte Yarroll: I plan to continue work on the Synoptic Key of Life for many years to come.

82
00:08:39.090 --> 00:08:42.120
La Monte Yarroll: I plan to take the site beta in just a few weeks.

83
00:08:45.870 --> 00:08:49.719
La Monte Yarroll: Here are a few development themes for my master's program.

84
00:08:50.370 --> 00:08:59.220
La Monte Yarroll: I recruited and coordinated several teams of fellow students. We planned our work, managed risk, and built trust by using the XP planning.

85
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:00.510
La Monte Yarroll: Via Trello.

86
00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:09.030
La Monte Yarroll: We used a wide range of open-source technologies, ranging from PostgreSQL to fine-tuning in SLM.

87
00:09:10.150 --> 00:09:13.429
La Monte Yarroll: For my last two classes, I leveraged clogged code.

88
00:09:13.690 --> 00:09:23.560
La Monte Yarroll: I maintained engineering discipline by using test-driven development, small increments, regression tests, and by applying linters and type checkers.

89
00:09:24.300 --> 00:09:37.200
La Monte Yarroll: I made key architectural decisions based on the availability of compute resources, using traditional classifiers where compute resources were constrained, only reserding to LLMs and SLMs.

90
00:09:37.650 --> 00:09:40.079
La Monte Yarroll: Where they offered unique capabilities.

91
00:09:42.950 --> 00:09:45.849
La Monte Yarroll: Here are links for those interested in diving deeper.

92
00:09:46.160 --> 00:09:47.060
La Monte Yarroll: Thank you.

